Size and proximity are two factors driving the price down, as is the fact the property has no planning permission for any form of structure beyond the remnants of a fort that can be seen only with the keenest eyes. 

Dun Mariag was once connected to the shore by a causeway and listing agent Vladi Private Islands say it's still possible to walk to from the mainland at the lowest tide. 

